ions in the owner class is tricky because it’s accessible in Groovy through meta properties, but private access is restricted. I’m contemplating the idea of using Groovy’s InvokerHelper or reflection, but I need to be cautious—reflection in tests might be banned.\\n\\nInstead, I could go with property access using InvokerHelper, which could be lighter than direct reflection. If I generate a class and manage the structure correctly, I might avoid complications. It seems like I need to create a manual bytecode or Java source as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying method logic**\\n\\nI'm looking into how class$ invocation works, and I see that any argument covers that. I'll get the response specification and use `InvokerHelper.getProperty` to access headerAssertions. \\n\\nThen, I’ll check if the matcher is an instance of Matcher; if it’s not, I’ll create an equivalent using `Matchers.equalTo`. Next, I'll instantiate HeaderMatcher, set the header name, and the matcher, and finally add it to the headerAssertions list. \\n\\nLastly, I’ll consider if the Closure call might handle argument passing. I’ll also want to check if the HeaderMatcher class has public setters via the javap tool.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DRVljDo2TBYxEnnTY8j5UW5d|fc_0dbdec28bdaa7dd3016a01895f67748194ab6e3aa38afb4570", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath 'tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/jacoco/effective/rest_assured_5_5_0_jar' -p io.restassured.assertion.HeaderMatcher | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7962, "output": 1084, "cacheRead": 96256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 105302, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778485581157, "responseId": "resp_0dbdec28bdaa7dd3016a01894dfd688194b6f3e187929322c6"}}
